dc_title_s: The road from London to York
dc_description_s: Extent: 1 map | Abstract: Map of a road from London to York via Stamford, Grantham, Newark-on-Trent, and Doncaster, depicted in ten narrow strips. Shows cities and towns, mile markers, rivers, and road junctions. | Notes: Relief shown pictorially.|North orientation varies. North arrows not shown.|Map detached from: The gentleman's magazine, and historical chronicle. Volume XXXVI : for the year M.CDD.LXVI. London : Printed for D. Henry and R. Cave, 1766. Map was originally published in the June 1766 issue.|Includes note. | Scale approximately 1:320,000
